fuelManagement - Variable in class net.dragondelve.customdriversutil.model.DriverBase
For now this parameter works in oval tracks only (but in future it will be extended to all track types); The higher the value, the more the AI will try to save fuel in some strategic situations instead of pushing, like when it sees it can maybe save a pit stop, it will try to stay in draft and coasting instead of overtaking while at the same time trying to not lose much distance to the race leader.
fuelManagement - Variable in class net.dragondelve.customdriversutil.model.xml.XMLDriver
